<article id="node-19513">
<h1 >1.1.T.45 Temporarily absent from a care situation</h1>
<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>This definition applies to all payments subject to assets testing provisions.</p>
<h2>Definition</h2>
<p>A person is temporarily absent from a care situation (<a href="../c/25">1.1.C.25</a>) IF their right to accommodation in the care situation is retained during their absence. This definition applies irrespective of where the person lives during the absence, including the principal home.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 11A(1) Principal home</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../../../4/6/3/70">4.6.3.70</a> Exempting the principal home - care situations</p>
</div>
